young people today, according to what they have to say for themselves, are just as enmeshed in civic and political life as the adolescents who came before them. American youth remain good citizens concerned about their communities and hopeful that they can help make a difference. But as The Evolving Citizen demonstrates, today’s youth understand and perform their roles as citizens differently because the world they live in has changed remarkably over the last half century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aPolitical participationzUnited States. 0aYouthxPolitical activityzUnited States. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican youth.  aJay P. Childers.  achange.  acitizen.  ademocracy.  aparticipation.  apolitics.  aunited states.  aus.  ausa.  ayoung adults.  a”democratic engagement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271060002?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271060002423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271060002/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK